2 HOUSE BILL 798
1 (A) THE MARYLAND OFFICE OF OVERDOSE RESPONSE, IN
2 COLLABORATION WITH THE DEPARTMENT, SHALL DEVELOP AND MAINTAIN AN
3 INTERACTIVE DASHBOARD ON OPIOID RESTITUTION FUND SPENDING FOR THE
4 PURPOSE OF SHARING PRESCRIPTION OPIOID–RELATED SETTLEMENT
5 INFORMATION WITH THE PUBLIC.
6 (B) THE DASHBOARD DEVELOPED AND MAINTAINED UNDER SUBSECTION
7 (A) OF THIS SECTION SHALL INCLUDE, DISAGGREGATED BY STATE, COUNTY, AND
8 MUNICIPALITY:
9 (1) PAYMENT SCHEDULE INFORMATION ON ESTIMATED PAYMENTS
10 TO THE STATE, COUNTY, OR MUNICIPALITY FROM OPIOID SETTLEMENTS;
11 (2) PAST SPENDING OF SETTLEMENT FUNDS;
12 (3) SPENDING PLANS AND PRIORITIES; AND
13 (4) A DETAILED DESCRIPTION OF ANY INITIATIVE FUNDED WITH
14 SETTLEMENT FUNDS, INCLUDING PERFORMANCE MEASURES IF APPLICABLE.
15 (C) THE DASHBOARD SHALL INCLUDE INFORMATION ON PUBLIC HEARINGS
16 CONDUCTED IN THE STATE, COUNTY, OR MUNICIPALITY REGARDING THE USE OF
17 SETTLEMENT FUNDS FROM THE OPIOID RESTITUTION FUND.
18 (D) (1) A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY RECEIVING SETTLEMENT FUNDS
19 SHALL PROVIDE TO THE DEPARTMENT THE NECESSARY FINANCIAL INFORMATION
20 RELATED TO SETTLEMENT FUNDING TO INCLUDE AS INFORMATION ON THE
21 DASHBOARD.
22 (2) INFORMATION REQUIRED TO BE PROVIDED UNDER PARAGRAPH
23 (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE IN COMPLIANCE WITH THE TERMS OF ANY
24 OPIOID–RELATED SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT.
25 (3) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH AN ONLINE PORTAL WITH
26 INSTRUCTIONS FOR A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY TO REPORT OR UPLOAD REQUIRED
27 INFORMATION TO THE DEPARTMENT FOR USE IN THE DASHBOARD.
28 (E) TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE, THE DASHBOARD SHALL USE EXISTING
29 PLATFORMS THAT PROVIDE DATA ON OPIOID USE AND OVERDOSES IN THE STATE.

HOUSE BILL 798 3
1 (F) THE DASHBOARD SHALL BE DEVELOPED AND MAINTAINED USING
2 FUNDS FROM THE OPIOID RESTITUTION FUND AS APPROPRIATED THROUGH THE
3 STATE BUDGET.
4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
5 October 1, 2025.

